title: Flight Simulator 2020 - POI's - Canada - Prince of Wales Tower
description:
In this video we will fly over the Prince of Wales Tower. The Prince of Wales Tower is the oldest martello tower in North America and is located in Point Pleasant Park, Halifax Regional Municipality, Nova Scotia, Canada. It was built in 1796 by Captain James Straton and was used as a redoubt and a powder magazine. Restored, it was designated a National Historic Site of Canada in 1943.
